info.title: Tag Manager API
info.description: API for accessing Tag Manager accounts and containers.

get.description: Lists all GTM Accounts that a user has access to.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the account in storage.

get.description: Lists all Containers that belongs to a GTM Account.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the container in storage.

get.description: Lists all GTM Macros of a Container.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the macro in storage.

get.description: Lists all GTM Rules of a Container.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the rule in storage.

get.description: Lists all GTM Tags of a Container.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the tag in storage.

get.description: Lists all GTM Triggers of a Container.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the trigger in storage.

get.description: Lists all GTM Variables of a Container.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the variable in storage.

get.description: Lists all Container Versions of a GTM Container.

parameters.name: containerVersionId
parameters.description: The GTM Container Version ID. Specify published to retrieve the currently published version.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the container version in storage.

parameters.name: fingerprint
parameters.description: When provided, this fingerprint must match the fingerprint of the container version in storage.

post.description: Restores a Container Version. This will overwrite the containers current configuration (including its macros, rules and tags). The operation will not have any effect on the version that is being served (i.e. the published version).

get.description: List all users that have access to the account along with Account and Container Permissions granted to each of them.

post.description: Creates a users Account & Container Permissions.

delete.description: Removes a user from the account, revoking access to it and all of its containers.

get.description: Gets a users Account & Container Permissions.

put.description: Updates a users Account & Container Permissions.
